sec.p:
Neeman et al. [18] reported the use of diffusion-encoding schemes that were made up of couples of gradients with positive and negative polarities in order to minimize a cross-term effect in the case of static field inhomogeneities. To minimize the scalar effects of the unknown cross-term effect of the background and the diffusion-encoding gradients, the geometric mean (gm) operation was used for both the positive and negative polarities of the diffusion-encoding gradients by applying the following equations [18, 19]:
